b'[<p><i><b>UFC 81: Breaking Point</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> (MMA) event held on February 2, 2008 by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> (UFC) at the <a href="/wiki/Mandalay_Bay_Events_Center" title="Mandalay Bay Events Center">Mandalay Bay Events Center</a> on the <a href="/wiki/Las_Vegas_Strip" title="Las Vegas Strip">Las Vegas Strip</a>.\n</p>, <p>The main event featured <a href="/wiki/Tim_Sylvia" title="Tim Sylvia">Tim Sylvia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Ant%C3%B4nio_Rodrigo_Nogueira" title="Ant\xc3\xb4nio Rodrigo Nogueira">Ant\xc3\xb4nio Rodrigo "Minotauro" Nogueira</a> for the UFC Interim World Heavyweight Championship. UFC Heavyweight champion <a href="/wiki/Randy_Couture" title="Randy Couture">Randy Couture</a> declined a championship fight with Nogueira,<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-couturedeclines_1-0"><a href="#cite_note-couturedeclines-1">[1]</a></sup> which resulted in the creation of the interim title.\n</p>, <p>This event also saw the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">UFC</a> debut of <a href="/wiki/WWE" title="WWE">WWE</a> wrestler <a href="/wiki/Brock_Lesnar" title="Brock Lesnar">Brock Lesnar</a> in a bout against former UFC <a href="/wiki/Heavyweight_(MMA)" title="Heavyweight (MMA)">heavyweight</a> champion <a href="/wiki/Frank_Mir" title="Frank Mir">Frank Mir</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-ufc_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-ufc-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>At the end of this event, $60,000 was awarded to each of the fighters who received one of these three awards.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFC81bonuses_5-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFC81bonuses-5">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>]'